text:
View of northern tip of Welfare Island, looking north east from No. 25 East End Ave., Manhattan, into Astoria L.I. Hell Gate Bridge may also be seen in the background.

About 1930.

Wurts Brothers.
title: Islands - Welfare Island.

text:
(1)
East River, north from East 76th (left) to East 80th Streets, showing John Jay Park, the East End Hotel for Women, and (extreme right) the 14-story apartment house No. 1 East End Ave., from East 79th to East 80th Streets.
April 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, including a view of East 79th Street, west from Exterior Street (Marie Curie Ave.), and the 15-story apartment house, the Yorkgate, No. 25 East End Ave., at the S.E. corner of East 80th Street.
April 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, as No. 1, at a later date.
Autumn 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
